public abstract class AbstractGridElementCreator
extends java.lang.Object
implements IGridElementCreator

Abstract imlementation of the IGridElementCreator interface. This implementation mainly delegates the canCreate(Object) method to an internal one and sets the internal object to the argument if the internal implementation returned true.

Method Detail

canCreate

public boolean canCreate(java.lang.Object fromObject)
Description copied from interface: IGridElementCreator
Ask this creator if it is able to create elements from the specified object. If this methods returns true the object will be remembered until another call of any of the canCreate(...) methods. This object can afterwards retrieved with the IGridElementCreator.getObject() method.

Specified by:
canCreate in interface IGridElementCreator
Parameters:
fromObject - The object from which to create an element.
Returns:
True if this creator is potentially able to create elements from the specified object.

getObject

public java.lang.Object getObject()
Description copied from interface: IGridElementCreator
Get the argument of the last successful call of any of the canCreate(...) methods. A successful call is a call that returned true.

Specified by:
getObject in interface IGridElementCreator
Returns:
The argument of the last successful call of a canCreate(...) method. This may be null if no such method was called before or if the argument was null itself. This method is used by IGridElementCreator.create(IGridContainer) to get the object from which to create the new element.
